# Outreach & email (LearnForge / EbookGamez)

## Partnership mail (SCORE, SBDC, nonprofits)

- **Never auto-send** partnership or mentorship emails without explicit user approval.
- Default workflow: **create a Gmail draft** (via Gmail MCP when available), not send.
- Always **CC `ebookgames@yahoo.com`** on partnership outreach.
- Optional Reply-To: `ebookgames@yahoo.com`.

## Signature block (use on all outreach)

```
Damond Morris
702-379-0396
ebookgames@yahoo.com
```

## Links in templates

- LearnForge games: `{PUBLIC_SITE_URL}/games` (use live origin when drafting)
- EbookGamez: `https://ebookgamez.com`

## Channel split

| Task | Tool |
|------|------|
| SCORE / SBDC / partner outreach | Gmail (draft → user sends) |
| Subscriber welcome & digests | Resend (server) |
| Replies & CC archive | Yahoo inbox |

## Reference files

- `docs/partnership-outreach-emails.md` — full templates
- `docs/email-setup-guide.md` — Resend env + Gmail MCP setup
- `artifacts/learnforge/src/pages/owner-outreach.tsx` — in-app copy hub

## Constraints

- No paid per-email APIs for games or bulk marketing beyond Resend free tier.
- Do not recommend licensing Kahoot/Blooket; build similar mechanics in-app.
- User sends partnership emails manually; AI drafts and copies only.
